   101	  Do you live outside the US?  If so, you're probably familiar with the
   102	 hassles of keeping up with the latest information - the three to five month
   103	 lead time for US publication, plus time for local book dealers to catalog
   104	 new releases, plus problems in trying to order... plus the delays while your
   105	 book comes in on special order, goes through Customs, the inevitable price
   106	 hikes through all the middlemen, taxes...  not only is DOSREF priced
   107	 well below the price of good printed computer books in the US, it's probably
   108	 far cheaper than you could expect to pay for US books locally.  Plus your
   109	 order will show up in your very own mailbox by air mail.
